<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1748,2014]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">Calyx longer than wide, widest near upper side of stomach (coinciding with conspicuous lateral expansions or wings) gradually narrowing towards upper part and towards stout stalk. No conspicuous gland cells observed in calyx. Stalk shows randomly arranged epithelial cells.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1748,2014]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">Gonads yellow, spherical, situated above lateral parts of stomach. Stomach pentagonal, slightly wider than long, pointed basally.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1748,2014]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,152,209]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="67" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">
Foot with rounded lateral wings slightly narrower at their base. Main foot gland spherical. Middle groove of foot clearly lined by glandular cells on both sides. Sometimes a lateral bud at level of lateral expansion of calyx; it can reach a considerable size relative to adult. Bud on 
<typeStatus box="[624,717,186,209]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">holotype</typeStatus>
<number box="[724,764,186,209]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" value="208.0">208</number>
µm total length, 
<number box="[947,987,186,209]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" value="104.0">104</number>
µm calyx width, 
<number box="[1175,1215,186,209]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" value="125.0">125</number>
µm calyx length.
</paragraph>
